## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Scope

This bug fix addresses a critical dependency issue where the VS Code extension command “Download Embedding Model” (KSA-104) fails when the MCP server is not running. The fix involves two changes:

1. **Extension rewrite**: Remove MCP server HTTP API dependency — extension downloads models directly from HuggingFace using VS Code’s built-in HTTP client
2. **Cache invalidation**: All 3 MCP server modules’ ModelRegistry classes cache registry.json in-memory at startup — newly downloaded models are invisible until server restart. Fix: re-read file on every getModel() call.

### 1.2 Out of Scope

* New model additions to catalog
* Download progress percentage
* Model deletion capability
* UI changes to QuickPick (same UX, different backend)

### 1.3 Preliminary Requirement

* **KSA-104** (Download Embedding Model feature) — the original feature this bug was found in
* **KSA-102** (Model Manager infrastructure) — provides ModelRegistry that needs cache fix

## 2. Business Requirements

### 2.1 Problem Statement

**Scenario**: Developer installs the extension fresh. No MCP server is running yet. Developer wants to download an embedding model to enable semantic search.

**Current behavior (broken)**: Extension calls POST /api/models/download on MCP server HTTP API → server not running → ECONNREFUSED → error message “Cannot reach MCP server” → user stuck in chicken-and-egg loop (needs model to start server, needs server to download model).

**Expected behavior (fixed)**: Extension downloads model directly from HuggingFace without needing MCP server. After download, MCP server (when started) immediately sees the new model without restart.

