### 2.4 List of User Stories

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| # | Story | Priority | Source |
| 1 | As a developer, I want to download embedding models even when MCP server is not running, so that I can set up the system from scratch | MUST HAVE | KSA-105 |
| 2 | As a developer, I want the MCP server to immediately recognize newly downloaded models without restart, so that I don’t need to restart the server after downloading a model | MUST HAVE | KSA-105 |

### 2.5 Details of User Stories

#### STORY 1: Download Models Without MCP Server

As a developer, I want to download embedding models even when MCP server is not running, so that I can set up the system from scratch

**Root Cause**: Extension delegates download to MCP server HTTP API. Server may not be running.

**Fix**: Extension performs download directly: 1. Read model catalog (hardcoded in extension) 2. Download files from HuggingFace using https.get() 3. Save to ~/.code-intel/models/{model-name}/ 4. Update ~/.code-intel/models/registry.json directly

**Acceptance Criteria:**

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| # | Criterion |
| AC-1 | Given MCP server is NOT running, when user invokes “Download Embedding Model”, then QuickPick shows model list (from local catalog, no server call) |
| AC-2 | Given user selects a model to download, then extension downloads directly from HuggingFace without calling MCP server |
| AC-3 | Given download completes, then registry.json is updated with model entry and active\_model set |
| AC-4 | Given download fails (network error), then clear error message shown to user |
| AC-5 | Given model already downloaded, then user can switch active model without MCP server |

#### STORY 2: MCP Server Cache Invalidation

As a developer, I want the MCP server to immediately recognize newly downloaded models without restart

**Root Cause**: ModelRegistry in all 3 MCP modules reads registry.json once at startup and caches in memory. When extension downloads a model and updates registry.json, the running MCP server doesn’t see the change.

**Fix**: ModelRegistry.getModel() (or equivalent property access) re-reads registry.json from disk on every call instead of using cached data.

**Acceptance Criteria:**

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| # | Criterion |
| AC-6 | Given MCP server is running, when extension downloads a new model and updates registry.json, then server’s next getModel() call returns the new model |
| AC-7 | Given MCP server is running, when extension switches active model in registry.json, then server’s next activeModel read returns the new active model |
| AC-8 | Given registry.json is modified externally, then all 3 MCP modules (Python, Node.js, Kotlin) reflect the change on next read |

