## 4. Risks and Assumptions

### 4.1 Risks

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| Extension HTTP client less robust than server-side | Medium | Low | Use Node.js https module (proven, stable) |
| Race condition: extension writes registry.json while server reads | Low | Low | JSON write is atomic (write temp → rename) |
| Performance: re-reading registry.json on every call | Low | Low | File is tiny (<1KB), OS caches in page cache |

### 4.2 Assumptions

* Extension has direct internet access to HuggingFace (no proxy issues)
* ~/.code-intel/models/ directory is writable by both extension and server processes
* Registry.json format remains backward-compatible

## 5. Non-Functional Requirements

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Category | Requirement |
| Reliability | Extension download works regardless of MCP server state |
| Performance | Registry re-read adds < 1ms overhead per call (file < 1KB) |
| Compatibility | Fix applied consistently across Python, Node.js, Kotlin modules |
| Backward Compat | Existing registry.json files remain valid after fix |

